    "A typical extension is the multi-agent deep deterministic policy gradient (MADDPG) [7].",
    "In MADDPG, the critic is a centralized Q-function designed to capture global information and coordinate learning signals.",
    "Meanwhile, the actors are local policies, ensuring decentralized execution.",
    "MADDPG assumes deterministic actors with continuous actions, allowing for the backpropagation of gradients from the value function to the policies.",
    "The gradient of each parameterized actor i (a i | o i) with learnable parameters i, abbreviated as i, is defined as follows:where D is the experience buffer that contains joint observation-action tuples⟨⃗ o, ⃗ a, ⃗ r, ⃗ o ′ ⟩."
